**Defines TypeScript types for the ARE installer workflow supporting installation to Claude Code, OpenCode, and Gemini runtime directories.**

## Exported Types

### Runtime
```typescript
type Runtime = 'claude' | 'opencode' | 'gemini' | 'all'
```
Discriminates between supported AI coding assistant runtimes: `'claude'` maps to `~/.claude` or `.claude`, `'opencode'` to `~/.config/opencode` or `.opencode`, `'gemini'` to `~/.gemini` or `.gemini`, `'all'` installs to all three.

### Location
```typescript
type Location = 'global' | 'local'
```
Discriminates installation scope: `'global'` targets user-level directories (`~/.claude`, `~/.config/opencode`, etc.), `'local'` targets project-level directories (`.claude`, `.opencode`, etc.).

### InstallerArgs
```typescript
interface InstallerArgs {
  runtime?: Runtime;
  global: boolean;
  local: boolean;
  uninstall: boolean;
  force: boolean;
  help: boolean;
  quiet: boolean;
}
```
Parsed CLI arguments for installer: `runtime` selects target (optional for prompting), `global`/`local` flags control installation scope, `uninstall` triggers removal, `force` overwrites existing files, `help` shows usage, `quiet` suppresses banner/info output.

### InstallerResult
```typescript
interface InstallerResult {
  success: boolean;
  runtime: Exclude<Runtime, 'all'>;
  location: Location;
  filesCreated: string[];
  filesSkipped: string[];
  errors: string[];
  hookRegistered?: boolean;
  versionWritten?: boolean;
}
```
Reports single runtime/location installation outcome: `success` indicates overall status, `runtime` excludes `'all'` (results are per-concrete-runtime), `filesCreated`/`filesSkipped` track file write operations, `errors` accumulates failure messages, `hookRegistered` is Claude-specific (settings.json registration), `versionWritten` confirms VERSION file creation.

### RuntimePaths
```typescript
interface RuntimePaths {
  global: string;
  local: string;
  settingsFile: string;
}
```
Resolved filesystem paths for a runtime: `global` points to user-level directory (`~/.claude`), `local` to project-level (`.claude`), `settingsFile` to settings.json for hook registration (Claude Code only).

## Integration Context
Used by `src/installer/operations.ts` (install/uninstall logic), `src/installer/paths.ts` (path resolution), `src/installer/prompts.ts` (interactive mode), and `src/installer/index.ts` (CLI entry point). The `Runtime` type's `'all'` variant requires expansion to concrete runtimes before producing `InstallerResult` instances.